President Jacob Zuma on Monday wished the Muslim community in South Africa a happy Eid al-Fitr. In a statement issued by the Presidency, Zuma said: We join our Muslim compatriots to celebrate the end of Ramadan, the Islamic holy month of fasting, and we wish all Muslims, Eid Mubarak. Eid al-Fitr is an important religious occasion celebrated by Muslims worldwide to mark the end of Ramadan, the Islamic holy month of fasting.